                        <div class="landing-page span8 grid">
                            <section class="content">
                                <h1 class="main-title">History</h1>
      	
		<div class="gridset">
          
          <article class="span4 box grid resize">
  <a href="/about-red-deer/history/history-of-red-deer/" target="_self"><img src="/media/reddeerca/about-red-deer/history/archives/DA270-350x200.jpg" alt="Red Deer Archives, DA270; Harvesting on Bower Farm, ca. 1912" /></a>
              <h3><a href="/about-red-deer/history/history-of-red-deer/" target="_self">History of Red Deer</a></h3>
				<p>Red Deer&rsquo;s history goes back over 100 years. Check out the history exhibits including photographs and old documents or learn some new facts and trivia about Red Deer.</p>
</article>
          			<article class="span4 box grid resize">
				<a href="/about-red-deer/history/archives/" target="_self"><img src="/media/reddeerca/about-red-deer/history/archives/P4706-350x200.jpg" alt="Red Deer Archives, P4706; Members of the Balmoral Women's Institute at a wedding shower, 1945" /></a>
				<h3><a href="/about-red-deer/history/archives/" target="_self">Archives</a></h3>
				<p>Acquires, preserves and makes available to the public both municipal and community records. Come explore our collections.</p>
			</article>
          			<article class="span4 box grid resize">
              <a href="/about-red-deer/history/heritage/" target="_self"><img src="/media/reddeerca/city-government/mayor-and-city-council/Original-City-Hall-and-Fire-Hall-350x200.jpg" alt="Original City Hall and Fire Hall 1912" /></a>
              <h3><a href="/about-red-deer/history/heritage/" target="_self">Heritage</a></h3>
				<p>Promoting and supporting heritage and culture defines us as a community, promotes a sense of belonging and allows us to recognize and celebrate the lives and achievements of former and current citizens. </p>
			</article>
          			<article class="span4 box grid resize">
              <a href="/city-government/mayor-and-city-councillors/past-mayor-and-councillors/" target="_self"><img src="/media/reddeerca/city-government/mayor-and-city-council/City-Council-photo-1967_1968_B-350x200.JPG" alt="City Council photo - 1967-1968" /></a>
              <h3><a href="/city-government/mayor-and-city-councillors/past-mayor-and-councillors/" target="_self">Past Mayors and Councillors</a></h3>
				<p>This section highlights the past and present Mayors and Councillors of the Town of Red Deer (1901 to 1913) and The City of Red Deer (1913 to present).</p>
			</article>
          
          
          
          
          
          
      </div><!--.gridset close--></section>
<!--exclude-section2-start-->
<section class="news-mod">
<h2 class="sub-title">News & Notices</h2>
<div class="gridset">
<article class="span4 grid">
	<h3><a href="/whats-happening/news-room/galbraith-pedestrian-bridge-replacement-starting-next-week.html">Galbraith pedestrian bridge replacement </a></h3>
	<p class="date">September 9, 2016</p>
	<p>Galbraith pedestrian bridge, which crosses the Waskasoo Creek close to the Red Deer River in Galbraith Park, will be closed starting Wednesday for replacement. </p>
</article><article class="span4 grid">
	<h3><a href="/whats-happening/news-room/city-hosts-emergency-services-memorial-march.html">City hosts Emergency Services ...</a></h3>
	<p class="date">September 8, 2016</p>
	<p>The public is invited to join Red Deer Emergency Services and the Royal Canadian Mounted Police (RCMP) for a Memorial March ceremony on Sunday, September 11, 2016.</p>
</article><article class="span4 grid">
	<h3><a href="/whats-happening/news-room/red-deer-and-district-fcss-releases-annual-report-.html">Red Deer and District FCSS releasess ...</a></h3>
	<p class="date">September 8, 2016</p>
	<p>Red Deer &amp; District Family and Community Support Services (FCSS) released its 2015 Annual Report, entitled &ldquo;Stone Soup &ndash; A Recipe for Community.&rdquo;</p>
</article></div><!--.gridset close-->
</section><!--.news-mod close-->
